// An `isolated` function is a function within which specific rules apply when accessing mutable state.
// An `isolated` function can access mutable state that is passed as a parameter.
// Such a function can access non-`isolated` module-level state only if the variable is `final` and
// the type is a subtype of `readonly` or `isolated object {}`.
// An `isolated` function can access `isolated` module-level variables within a `lock` statement.
// Any function or method call in an `isolated` function should also be calling an `isolated` function or method.
